  "text": "We contend that the use of ICP analysis on forensic soil/ sediment samples to derive results that can be interpreted to provide an indication of provenance poses a significant problem that has not been addressed by Pye et al. [CITATION_1] due to the requirement of homogenisation of samples prior to analysis. As mentioned above, it is not possible to identify pre-, syn-or postevent mixing and thus the derived conclusions cannot be tested.",
